@huangzh13, please check out the latest commit [4522d6772dd1d56b9eb073e4ea23c51562064812](https://github.com/akanimax/BMSG-GAN/commit/4522d6772dd1d56b9eb073e4ea23c51562064812) which fixes the memory leak in the "wgan-gp" loss calculation. Also, in order for WGAN-GP to work, you need to tune the learning rates of the Discriminator and Generator differently. Try the values of:
`g_lr = 0.003` and `d_lr = 0.0003`.
Hope this helps.

Please let me know how it works out. :+1: 

Best regards,
@akanimax

@huangzh13, As I could understand, you wrote that you were not getting results at all. If you had mentioned that you have obtained good results using `RaHinge`, I wouldn't have written so. Also, I didn't say that you are impatient :smile:. 

About this, I have mentioned in the paper, that With RaHinge or with other Relativistic versions of losses, you don't have to tune the learning rate so much, and that's why we used RaHinge loss. Could you please share your high resolution results with RaHinge? It would be helpful for others as well.

Best regards,
@akanimax
